According to the data, the job search season didn't start well, but it wasn't a total disaster.

Boss Zhipin's "talent trends in the 10 days after Spring Festival 2020" shows that in the 10 days after Spring Festival this year (2.3-2.12) , the demand for new jobs in the job market has halved compared with the same period in 2019, with small and micro enterprises with fewer than 100 employees most affected, the demand for new talent dropped sharply by 61% .

And of those who left years ago and started looking years later, more than half favour,-person companies.

The enthusiasm of the talent side was less affected by the epidemic than the demand side, and 47 percent of job seekers started intensive job-hunting by Feb. 3 as planned, according to BOSS Zhipin's post-spring festival job-hunting survey 2020, 16.5% started job hunting on the 6th and 7th day of the Lunar New Year. In addition, only 20% of the job-hopping considered to give up or delay the job change.

Since February 10, all over the work has been approved one by one since the resumption of new recruitment demand has begun to resume. Those considering giving up or postponing the job hunt are in the minority, and many more are already gearing up to scour job sites, search for tweets..

That's life. No matter what year it is, it goes on.

Dindin

CITY: Hohhot

Working age: Five years

Dindin had always believed that the experience of life was more important than the outcome.

So whether she left the Internet company to become a journalist or the media to find her next opportunity, she made choices with little regret.

Six months ago, she left her former employer to study abroad. Although she had planned to take the IELTS exam, she spent most of the three months after her resignation on her way to see the world. By the time she got back to her desk in Inner Mongolia and began to read, hohhot has already had its first snow in 2019.

Back home, Dindin learned to tutor her teenage brother, Cook with her girlfriends, and walk the dog. Beijing's life and the rhythm of the anxiety, gradually by this insipid life dissipation.

"For the first two months after I quit my job, I had to get up almost every night at 1:30 to order a hundred-dollar barbecue, wake up at noon and order half a roast duck, knowing that it would gradually turn into a pig, and still couldn't stop myself from staying up until 4 or 5 o'clock reading novels and eating until my stomach hurt, " she recalled in her "resignation diary. " Later, when she recalled that time, the more indulgent she was, the more anxious and confused she became.

Looking back, if it had happened again, Dindin would have said No.

But after that stage, the current anxiety about finding a job while looking for the next one is real.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, Dindin saw a letter from the Qichun County People's Hospital in Hubei Province among her college alumni. She and her good friend's tacit understanding for many years immediately came on the line, and began to collect materials and aid for the medical staff of the Hubei County Hospital. She changed her wechat nickname to "mask off to Dindin" and set off with a passion for "something to do" .

For two weeks, under the leadership of Dindin and his partners, masks, protective clothing, alcohol and other supplies were sent to Anju town, Yangping town, Hongshan town, Fangzui town, Yingshan County, Tuanfeng, far mountain, Khingan and other towns in Hubei, which are not common in people's sight. Most of the money for the purchase came from white collar students like Dindin, 35,70,105 such a transfer of funds together.

After officials began combing through supplies again, Dindin and his partners released financial details and the flow of supplies, ending the project.

It was then that Dindin began to worry about himself. An interview at a company he had promised years earlier had been postponed because of the epidemic, and the position had been canceled altogether.

Dindin began the long awaited job search trilogy: Boss Zhipin Brush, resume, and so on.

"No matter what thrilling and passionate stories we may have had, in the end we must all return to our normal lives and long for a return to normal order. "

The day before the 15th day of the first lunar month, another company accepted Dindin's resume and said it would arrange a video interview as soon as possible if the conversation went well.

Dindin hopes to find a job before the epidemic is over, and all previous adventures and romances will have to give way to survival.

Ari

CITY: Beijing

Working age: 4 years

Ari's job search has been going on for six months.

Ari, a former buyer for an internet company, has been looking for work in recent months.

When she resigned naked from a big platform last August, Ari had no idea the gap would be so long. "The idea was that it had been a tough year and I wanted to take a break. "

Psychological expectations was originally a month or two, "gold nine silver ten" how will have a new job, later she found that the market situation is worse than she thought.

Ari only had one weekend off between his first two jobs. There wasn't much room for growth in the previous company. My friend gave me a chance to push in, so I left the company on Friday and took the new job on Monday.

But this time, Ari took a long vacation.

Ari may not be a Newbie, but over the past winter, her career radar has suddenly gone off.

Some platforms send out resumes without much response, and those that do are not very optimistic. In the original push when the advantage of the resume, this time also encountered a "no recruitment" of the embarrassment.

Although there have been interviews over the past few months, Ari has never been able to find the right job, and the right one is almost impossible to fill -- as if there were no job openings at Harvard, and Ari was reluctant to go.

The last interview years ago, to the end of the interview, the position lost.

Many cities have announced policies to delay the resumption of work, Ari can not stay in his hometown. On Feb. 2, the day before a group of companies went online, she returned to her home in Beijing and began scouring job recruitment websites.

While the number of jobs being released is small, companies are also updating their job listings on their websites.

Ari changed his resume overnight, hoping that the next day's bosses would see his information when they turned on the system.

"I would like to go to some companies, but there are no suitable positions available, I will also take the initiative to leave a message, BOSS Zhipin on the general will have a reply. " Ari said, now she brush BOSS Zhipin, is also a way to alleviate anxiety.

In the procurement business, where many resources are national, changing cities can be more life-changing for Ari than it can be at work.

In addition to her position in Beijing, Ari has also started reading about Shanghai, Nanjing and Zhengzhou. Zhengzhou is close to her hometown, and Nanjing is her favorite city all along. If she does not see the right opportunity in the near future, she wants to take advantage of this opportunity, or simply change a city life, work.

Hyo-woo

Working age: 8 years

Xiaoyu graduated from the first job nearly 5 years, and then seamless transition to the second job nearly 3 years. Originally intended to quit the rest to find a job, but catch up with the family need to take care of, he just stayed at home for a period of time, ready to look for a job years later.

Leaving his last job in the traditional education industry, Xiaoyu's concern was personal career development. The departure would have been earlier, but the company had an important branding event to launch, the immediate family leader took maternity leave, and Xiaoyu gave up the opportunity to stay at another company for a few more months.

By the time he left office last May, Naked Xiaoyu was anxious and confused.

"I feel like I'm so bad, I can't keep up. "

In order to alleviate anxiety, Xiao Yu randomly found a company on the two-month work, the result is of course inappropriate. Take advantage of the new year, Xiaoyu resigned in time to stop losses. "The consequences of anxiety are too heavy. It's better to get down to earth and take your time. "

Two years ago, Xiaoyu enrolled in an online course on basic internet operations, running the course from theory to practice over a four-week period. Some of the students in the college were young graduates, there is a part of the same as Xiao Yu want to change the line of "middle-aged workplace. ".

Because of the impact of the epidemic, the old owner prepared for several years did not get on-line business, was forced on-line, the original company's other department boss, also hope Xiaoyu back.

Although the new job is not yet in sight, Xiaoyu does not intend to go back, he made up his mind to go to the Internet company. "A lifetime is a lifetime, so studying hard is bound to pay off. "

For the current situation, Xiao Yu is not so anxious. The process of making yourself stronger and more competitive takes time, and for those who aren't prepared enough, "gold, three silver, and four silver" is just more time to be hit by the boss and HR.

In the end, Xiaoyu added: "I also want to understand one thing, admit that he is an ordinary person, especially important. "

He said he used to think that if he worked hard, he would be different, and could even save the Earth. But now he realized that ordinary people don't make their own decisions, and that only by working hard can they have a better chance of getting better.

"I know it's not easy, but I still want to refuel after I figure it out. "

I didn't think I'd have to do it this way.

Wake Up

CITY: Zhengzhou

Working age: 2 years

Wake up now, the biggest regret is not to take the computer back home.

She was caught off guard by the fact that she was a recruiter for an Internet advertising agency and would have to work from home for years.

Now the company is about, people, then to expand the business, years after a large number of recruitment plans to promote. The seventh day of the first lunar month, wake up and colleagues to start online office. For the past week or so, because of the traffic restrictions, I've been using my phone to communicate with job seekers online, screen candidates, arrange video interviews, and so on, all through BOSS Zhipin's mobile APP.

"I wasn't used to it at first, I couldn't even type fast enough, but it took me half a day to set it up. "

During last September and October's job-hunting season, when the company had 50 interviews a day at its peak, the experience of waking up and the way you work changed as everything shifted online.

"when a candidate comes to the company for an interview, it's also how he learns about the company and builds trust in the company, " he says, the amount of information is equivalent to the first face, some even more than the first face. "In any case, I touch my phone as soon as I wake up in the morning, I turn it on and I start to answer messages, and at night, it's a peak time for communication. "

Even so, there are some candidates who will resist a video interview for one reason or another. "maybe it is inconvenient where he is, like my colleagues who are now mostly in Henan and can't get out of the village. "

"In the past week, we have found that very few people have come out to look for a job. Most of them will concentrate on looking for a job after the 15th day of the first lunar month, " he said. Despite the video interview process, wake up in the past week, the number of invited interviews and actual face-to-face are lower than expected, "every day in the BOSS Zhipin about 100 people volunteered to chat, specific statistics have not done detailed. "

Wake up's company is in a period of rapid development, need to increase the production of video staff, although the difficulty increases, people still have to recruit. According to wakening past experience, most of the recruits in September and October are fresh graduates. The spring recruitment is the main way to find fast-track and relatively experienced employees.

So far today, wake up has completed the recruitment of 15 employees, waiting for the news of the overall resumption of work, can arrange for staff entry. Two of the positions are in desperate need and have joined the team online.

With an epidemic, workers across the country are facing huge uncertainty as they prepare for their spring job hunt. This is unnerving.

Small and medium-sized companies in the accommodation and catering, wholesale and retail, tourism, commerce and trade sectors have been hit hard by the outbreak, but new opportunities have also opened up in the logistics, health care and education sectors.

The changes in the job market certainly don't stop there, as more companies raise the threshold for talent reserves and absorb the largest number of new graduates, reducing overall demand. The effects of this season may continue into the second half of the year, affecting the fall season.

In other words, for those who are ready, a job-hunting season, when competition intensifies, is a tougher-than-expected copy. But for the unprepared, there is more to do than worry and confusion.

Some people take advantage of this moment, the truth of their job-hunting Skills Package, adjust the direction of the job search.

Some people figure out that they're quitting their jobs just to escape the drudgery of working from home and looking for ways to improve their productivity.

Local offline job fairs have been cancelled, and new graduates have started to use online recruitment channels even earlier..

Anxiety seems to be a cloud over all job seekers, but everyone has their own day to live, their own pace and persistence.

For example, in the case of Dindin in the epidemic to put their efforts to work overtime into the volunteer program, Ari to broaden their horizons to other cities, Xiaoyu while enriching themselves while waiting for the opportunity to persist, waking Up is the "BOSS" of a Cyberman holding a mobile phone to interview a candidate.

This year's "gold three silver four" may not be so shiny, but destined to be extraordinary.

May you find your own light.

And I wish you health and safety.
